captions.text: ("Fur Elise")

- [Voiceover] There are six
types of guy friends you have.

Here's the guy who's got
his (bleep) together.
He's always there whenever you need help.
- Need some help?
- [Voiceover] Like when are taxes due?
- April 15th.
- [Voiceover] Where should I grab dinner?

- There's a great new
Indian restaurant downtown.

- [Voiceover] Who's your
favorite Kardashian?

- None, there are way
better things on television.
- [Voiceover] But if you had to pick.
- Khloe, obviously.

- [Voiceover] Then there's
the guy who you try to fix.
He always needs your help,
even if he's not totally aware of it.
Talk to her.
- What? No.

- [Voiceover] Hey,
Allison, he thinks you look
really nice today.
- Thank you. See you soon.
- Bye.
Maybe I should invite her over.
Should probably tidy up the place a bit.

- [Voiceover] Yes, your
project is a success.
- I bet my mom will clean it for me.
- [Voiceover] (sighs)
Next up, the guy who makes you laugh.

He's the first person
you'd invite to a party.
- Little girl!

- [Voiceover] If he's not
throwing a party himself.
- Oh, you're too skinny.
(laughter)

- [Voiceover] The one
thing he takes seriously
are things that, well, aren't serious.
(laughter)

- [Voiceover] But there's also
the guy who pisses you off.

He's the last person
you'd invite to a party.
- Well OK, I'm just saying
I have my own opinion. You have yours.
Just respect that.
I always feel like I'm being attacked.

- [Voiceover] For some
reason he's just cool enough
to still be your friend.

He has zero clue how bad he
can come across to others.

- Hey you know, hey, the
lady is not interested
so back the (bleep) off.
- [Voiceover] Well, at least he's honest.
- You OK?
- [Voiceover] Honesty isn't something
you'd associate with the guy who's
secretly in love with you.
- So what are your plans this weekend?

- [Voiceover] It's especially
bad when he happens to be
your close friend.
- I was thinking of seeing a movie.
- [Voiceover] He acts like your friend,
but he doesn't know that you know
that he wants to be more than friends.
- There's a new animated film out.

I can't remember if it's
Disney or DreamWorks.
- [Voiceover] Every time you're alone,
things potentially get super awkward.
- So, did you wanna invite anyone else?
- [Voiceover] Yes, you do.
- (laughs) That's cool.
Yeah, we can all get something
to eat afterwards or something.

- [Voiceover] Last, but
definitely not least,
the guy you're secretly in love with.
Every moment with him is torture.
- I think you got something--
- [Voiceover] Your heart stops.
- stuck in your teeth.
Might be parsley. (laughs)

- [Voiceover] (sighs)
He almost touched you.
Does that mean he likes you?
- Well, what do you think about it?
- [Voiceover] Wait, you weren't listening.
What did he say?
Just agree enthusiastically.

- Really? I don't really
care much for it at all.
- [Voiceover] Shit, you idiot.
You must look so dumb right now.
- You OK?
- [Voiceover] Act completely normal.
- Oh, you're just acting a little weird.

- [Voiceover] Ugh, that's
the opposite of normal.
- Not that weird's a bad thing.

- [Voiceover] Yes, he
totally loves you back.
You're going to be together forever.
Nope, never mind, he likes her
and you're gonna be forever alone.
But we all know that's not true
because you'll at least have these

six types of guys friends
to help you find out
who you really are.
